                "href": "/profile/Juliano-Oselame-1"
            },
            "answer_text": "Except, they aren\u2019t. I\u2019m writing this on a 4-year old HP notebook. There\u2019s absolutely nothing wrong with it. This computer is working the same way it was the day I took it out of the box. Even the screen is perfect. There isn\u2019t a single dead pixel on it!!! And this is not a top product. It\u2019s a computer from their budget line. It is a cheap computer. But only in price. Regarding its quality, it couldn\u2019t be better! My first laptop was an Acer. And it was a huge disappointment. The thing died on me after only 2 years of use. My brother had 2 Dell notebooks. One after the other. And both died on him after a few months of use. With HP, I never had such problems. HP has millions of computers out there. I don\u2019t have the official numbers here. But if you take the percentage of their machines that work perfectly, you\u2019ll see it is much bigger than those that fail. People must stop assuming that everything not sporting an Apple logo is rubbish. And BTW, Apple newest line of computers are not that impressive. The time Apple was innovative and unbeatable in quality is long gone. ",
