            "answer_text": "I do agree that they aren\u2019t very durable (my newest one has that hinge problem someone wrote about where the screw falls out for no reason and the screen just grinds cracks and pops when opening and closing. Seriously, it makes me cringe to hear the sound, because one of these times its just going to kill the motherboard). However, I don\u2019t think they\u2019re bad otherwise. Especially their high end models. As a matter of fact, their old DV6 model computers are some of the most durable laptops I\u2019ve seen.  (This is the model I have) This computer is used every day in a school environment. Falling, hitting lockers, dropped on tables, smacking each stair in it\u2019s bag as I walk up and down sometimes. And the only damage is a small crack in the silver lining (which I glued together), and the left click button was damaged although it is still functional (because I played too many clicker games on it). This computer is an absolute beast, especially for still running 9 years later with no hardware issues. It\u2019s even relatively fast despite it\u2019s Core 2 Duo at 2.1 GHz. The lower end consumer laptops tend to be fragile, though. ",
