                "name": "Braden Dodge",
                "href": "/profile/Braden-Dodge"
            },
            "answer_text": "A better question would be why are HP CONSUMER computers so bad. I actually really like HPs business line of laptops (EliteBooks / ProBooks). But yes, their consumer lines leave much to be desired. Most of the issues with their laptops have to do with CPUs and GPUs without adequate cooling methods. HPs are notorious for overheating, partly due to poor overall design and lack of planning for adequate ventilation, and partly due to cheap and poor quality thermal compound and solder. HP doesn't care about their consumer grade stuff because they know the big bucks are made from their business contracts. So that's where they invest all their money and efforts. ",
