            "answer_text": "I have been a computer service technician in a big box chain, and while we did get returns and had some issues with their low end refurbished systems. I chose an HP laptop due to it\u2019s quality and repairability. Later, I performed depot warranty repair for their laptops. I will say, that the quality of the line of laptops I was working on were subpar, the contractor who built them was not the best, while the other HP laptop line was solid, it was built by another company. I bought a laptop that I knew was from the other line. One thing that struck me about their laptops was that they provide the repair manuals and parts online. So, after warranty, you can repair your computer still. That being said, I have found other manufacturers doing the same. HP, in my experience, doesn't seem to be worse than any other manufacturer for it\u2019s price point. ",
